{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2945a50-449d-4ee5-a7a4-53cb035d7854","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**After updating**, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) — NuGet packages targeting `net10.0` may also need updates to versions that support `net11.0`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bed60e4d-5baa-48f6-9aa4-2bba24930ec8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search files since they described their setup.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **csproj**: `<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>`\n2. **global.json**: SDK version to `11.0.100`\n3. **Dockerfile**: Update base images to `:11.0` tags\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":362,"requestId":"D82B:229004:6446866:6D759A0:69F1626B"},"id":"94d2befe-12e3-4d87-b71f-5e95edd66d6b","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:44:18.680Z","parentId":"8275a854-f17f-4a15-a71e-c5384af0c6a5"}
